{"id": "EUVD-2022-55884", "enisaUuid": "0b3550a6-46fb-3f28-9688-9764e79376ec", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ncrypto: hisilicon/zip - fix mismatch in get/set sgl_sge_nr\n\nKASAN reported this Bug:\n\n\t[17619.659757] BUG: KASAN: global-out-of-bounds in param_get_int+0x34/0x60\n\t[17619.673193] Read of size 4 at addr fffff01332d7ed00 by task read_all/1507958\n\t...\n\t[17619.698934] The buggy address belongs to the variable:\n\t[17619.708371]  sgl_sge_nr+0x0/0xffffffffffffa300 [hisi_zip]\n\nThere is a mismatch in hisi_zip when get/set the variable sgl_sge_nr.\nThe type of sgl_sge_nr is u16, and get/set sgl_sge_nr by\nparam_get/set_int.\n\nReplacing param_get/set_int to param_get/set_ushort can fix this bug.", "datePublished": "2025-12-30T15:30:26", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-30T15:30:26", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d88b88514ef28515ccfa1f1787c2aedef75a79dd", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/272093471305261c4e07a2fc97c2d1e53cd56819", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f8a983d6e01b198320d310cb1326364d7d973b2a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5eaebd19fbb0e26e73a34f55d3b1dc310df0eb15", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d74f9340097a881869c4c22ca376654cc2516ecc", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50814"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50814"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "2ec0461e-d714-3430-92bf-03ea8926846b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "2fb6e3d3-e789-3a24-88e4-60a221d4efc7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0.3"}, {"id": "58d0fdb4-6d18-3c3c-b4ce-8d88299b6d49", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "f081fda293ffba54216a7dab66faba7275475006 <5eaebd19fbb0e26e73a34f55d3b1dc310df0eb15"}, {"id": "8338c410-db36-3ac6-b1d1-58ae22b5349d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "f081fda293ffba54216a7dab66faba7275475006 <d74f9340097a881869c4c22ca376654cc2516ecc"}, {"id": "87